(155, '_site_transient_wp_plugin_dependencies_plugin_data', 'a:3:{s:9:\"cartflows\";a:35:{s:4:\"name\";s:66:\"CartFlows – Funnel Builder &amp; Checkout Plugin for WooCommerce\";s:4:\"slug\";s:9:\"cartflows\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"3.1.2\";s:6:\"author\";s:78:\"<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/brainstormforce/\">Brainstorm Force</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:47:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/brainstormforce/\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:2:{s:10:\"sujaypawar\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:42:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/sujaypawar/\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:120:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fef0265f2dbea4aabd6a911cfa85e901883051a1bd92ebdb10d0268b74c60d0f?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:10:\"sujaypawar\";}s:9:\"wpcrafter\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/wpcrafter/\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:120:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/eba13a79e8d17f5009d9f0acff50de71b78a05b86e3288d09f2cf815c270d00f?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:16:\"Adam @ WPCrafter\";}}s:8:\"requires\";s:3:\"5.8\";s:6:\"tested\";s:5:\"6.9.4\";s:12:\"requires_php\";s:3:\"7.2\";s:16:\"requires_plugins\";a:0:{}s:6:\"rating\";i:96;s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:457;i:4;i:13;i:3;i:7;i:2;i:5;i:1;i:15;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:497;s:11:\"support_url\";s:47:\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/cartflows/\";s:15:\"support_threads\";i:1;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:1;s:15:\"active_installs\";i:200000;s:12:\"last_updated\";s:21:\"2026-06-26 9:44am GMT\";s:5:\"added\";s:10:\"2018-11-30\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:22:\"https://cartflows.com/\";s:8:\"sections\";a:6:{s:11:\"description\";s:14968:\"<h3>The #1 WordPress Funnel Builder &amp; WooCommerce Checkout Plugin</h3>\n<p>CartFlows is the #1 WordPress funnel builder and WooCommerce checkout plugin—trusted by over 200,000 stores worldwide. Since 2018, CartFlows has helped eCommerce sellers, course creators, agencies, and entrepreneurs turn their WooCommerce stores into high-converting revenue machines.</p>\n<p>Your WooCommerce checkout should do more than just work—it should <strong>convert</strong>. CartFlows replaces the clunky default WooCommerce checkout with a sleek, distraction-free, conversion-optimized experience that helps you sell more and maximize average order value (AOV) with every transaction.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://try.new/cartflows\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Try the live demo of CartFlows</a></p>\n<h3>The Affordable ClickFunnels Alternative Built for WordPress</h3>\n<p>Tired of paying $97–$297/month for SaaS funnel builders like ClickFunnels? CartFlows gives you all the same power—unlimited funnels, upsells, order bumps, A/B testing, and analytics—directly inside WordPress, at a fraction of the cost. No monthly SaaS fees. No lock-in. Full control over your data.</p>\n<h3>Why Your WooCommerce Store Needs CartFlows</h3>\n<p>The default WooCommerce checkout is functional, but far from modern. It lacks the speed, personalization, and seamless experience today&#8217;s customers expect. A clunky checkout loses sales every day, and nobody wants that.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s where CartFlows steps in. With CartFlows, you can:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Build a complete WordPress sales funnel without ever leaving your dashboard</li>\n<li>Replace WooCommerce&#8217;s default checkout with a modern, conversion-focused page</li>\n<li>Add one-click upsells, downsells, and dynamic order bumps to every funnel</li>\n<li>Create a one-page checkout, two-step checkout, or multi-step checkout flow</li>\n<li>Import professionally designed funnel templates in one click and go live in minutes</li>\n<li>Track funnel performance with built-in analytics and a revenue insights dashboard</li>\n<li>Automate post-purchase workflows, follow-up emails, and lead nurturing</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"750\" height=\"422\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/k96jHP9CaYA?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span>\n<p><a href=\"https://cartflows.com/whats-new/?utm_source=WordPress&amp;utm_medium=Referral&amp;utm_campaign=CF_description\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">What&#8217;s New</a> | <a href=\"https://cartflows.com/docs/?utm_source=WordPress&amp;utm_medium=Referral&amp;utm_campaign=CF_description\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Docs</a> | <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@CartFlows/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Video Tutorials</a> | <a href=\"https://cartflows.com/support/open-a-ticket/?utm_source=WordPress&amp;utm_medium=Referral&amp;utm_campaign=CF_description\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Get Help</a> | <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/cartflows\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Community</a></p>\n<h3>What Makes CartFlows Unique?</h3>\n<p><strong>Built for WooCommerce:</strong> CartFlows is the ultimate checkout plugin and WordPress funnel builder—designed from the ground up to work seamlessly within your existing WooCommerce setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Seamless page builder integration:</strong> Works with Elementor, Spectra, Bricks, Divi, Beaver Builder, Gutenberg, and more.</p>\n<p><strong>Effortless setup:</strong> Pre-designed funnel templates and drag-and-drop editing mean you can build high-converting funnels without touching a line of code.</p>\n<p><strong>Revenue boosters:</strong> One-click upsells, downsells, and order bumps help maximize your store&#8217;s average order value (AOV) on every transaction.</p>\n<p><strong>Modern checkout styles:</strong> Replace WooCommerce&#8217;s default checkout with sleek, branded layouts—one-column, two-column, multi-step, or instant checkout—all optimized for conversions.</p>\n<p><strong>Affordable:</strong> Get advanced funnel builder features without the hefty price tag of SaaS tools like ClickFunnels or Kajabi.</p>\n<h3>How It Works</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Install CartFlows:</strong> Activate the WordPress funnel builder from your WordPress dashboard.</li>\n<li><strong>Choose a template:</strong> Pick a professionally designed sales funnel and checkout template.</li>\n<li><strong>Customize your funnel:</strong> Use your favorite page builder to craft a seamless checkout experience.</li>\n<li><strong>Add dynamic offers:</strong> Boost revenue with personalized upsells, downsells, and order bumps.</li>\n<li><strong>Optimize with insights:</strong> Use CartFlows&#8217; analytics to refine your funnels and improve performance.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>💪 Powerful Features</h3>\n<h3>CartFlows Free Features</h3>\n<h4>1. Modern Checkout Styles</h4>\n<p>Replace the boring default WooCommerce checkout with a clean, conversion-focused experience that keeps buyers moving forward.</p>\n<h4>2. Instant Layouts</h4>\n<p>Skip the design work and launch a fully optimized sales funnel in minutes with professionally designed, ready-to-use layouts for every funnel step.</p>\n<h4>3. Multi-Page Builder Support</h4>\n<p>No matter your favorite page builder—Spectra, Elementor, Bricks, or Beaver—CartFlows works seamlessly with them all. Build beautiful, high-converting funnels your way, without limits or friction.</p>\n<h4>4. Override Store Checkout</h4>\n<p>Replace the default WooCommerce checkout with a streamlined, branded checkout experience. Whether it&#8217;s a single-step, two-step, or multi-step checkout, CartFlows gives you complete control over the WooCommerce checkout page—without writing a single line of code.</p>\n<h4>5. Import Ready-Made Sales Funnels</h4>\n<p>Why build from scratch? Import pre-made, conversion-optimized sales funnel templates with one click and start selling immediately. Every template is fully customizable using your page builder of choice.</p>\n<h4>6. Checkout Form Field Editor</h4>\n<p>Customize your WooCommerce checkout form fields with ease. Add, remove, reorder, or create custom fields to match your business needs and create a frictionless checkout experience that converts.</p>\n<h4>7. Social Media Pixel Tracking</h4>\n<p>Track customer actions across your entire funnel with built-in support for Google, Facebook, Pinterest, Snapchat, and TikTok pixels. Get deeper ad insights, retarget smarter, and turn more ad clicks into completed purchases.</p>\n<h4>8. Automations with OttoKit</h4>\n<p>Connect CartFlows to OttoKit to automate post-purchase workflows—send thank you emails, tag customers, notify your team, and manage leads—all without leaving WordPress. Integrates with 1,000+ apps including Gmail, Slack, Mailchimp, and more.</p>\n<h3>CartFlows Pro Features</h3>\n<h4>1. One-Click Upsells &amp; Downsells</h4>\n<p>Show customers a perfectly timed post-purchase upsell offer they can accept with a single click—no re-entering payment details. Increase your average order value on every transaction with dynamic upsell paths that respond to what customers already bought.</p>\n<h4>2. Dynamic Order Bumps</h4>\n<p>Boost revenue with personalized order bumps placed right on the WooCommerce checkout page. Use smart rules to show the most relevant offer based on cart contents, total, or customer history. Features multiple modern order bump styles and custom placement options.</p>\n<h4>3. A/B Split Testing</h4>\n<p>Test multiple versions of your checkout pages, upsell offers, order bumps, and headlines to find what converts best. Make data-driven decisions and continuously optimize every step of your WordPress sales funnel.</p>\n<h4>4. Advanced Funnel Analytics</h4>\n<p>Track conversions, revenue per funnel step, average order value, and customer behavior from a unified analytics dashboard. Identify underperforming steps and make targeted improvements to maximize your store&#8217;s revenue.</p>\n<h4>5. Smart Funnel Routing</h4>\n<p>Create personalized funnel journeys based on what&#8217;s in the customer&#8217;s cart or their purchase history. Smart Funnel Routing dynamically directs buyers to the most relevant upsell path—increasing the likelihood of conversion at every step.</p>\n<h4>6. Google Address Autocomplete</h4>\n<p>Speed up checkout by letting customers autocomplete their shipping and billing address with Google Maps integration. Fewer keystrokes means fewer drop-offs—especially on mobile.</p>\n<h4>7. Auto Apply Coupons</h4>\n<p>Stop making customers hunt for discount codes. With Auto Apply Coupons, discounts are applied automatically at checkout when conditions are met—creating a smoother buying experience and reducing cart abandonment.</p>\n<h4>8. Lead Generation Tools</h4>\n<p>Build your email list while making sales. CartFlows&#8217; built-in opt-in pages and lead capture features let you create high-converting landing pages and squeeze pages that feed leads directly into your email marketing platform.</p>\n<h4>9. Product Options</h4>\n<p>Let customers personalize their purchase right at checkout—choose sizes, colors, quantities, or add-ons. With highlight product and quantity selection controls, you can present choices in a way that feels helpful, not overwhelming.</p>\n<h4>10. Enhanced Subscription Handling</h4>\n<p>Selling recurring products? CartFlows integrates with WooCommerce Subscriptions to handle auto-payment retries, proration for upgrades, and seamless subscription checkout flows.</p>\n<h4>11. Conversion-Focused Funnel Templates</h4>\n<p>Access the full library of premium, professionally designed sales funnel templates for every use case—eCommerce, courses, memberships, lead generation, and more. Import any template with one click and customize it with your page builder.</p>\n<h4>12. Add Unlimited Funnel Steps</h4>\n<p>Build complete, multi-step sales funnels with upsells, downsells, thank-you pages, opt-in steps, and more. With CartFlows Pro, there&#8217;s no limit to the number of funnels or steps you can create.</p>\n<h3>✅ Who Can Benefit from CartFlows?</h3>\n<p>CartFlows is the perfect WordPress funnel builder and WooCommerce checkout plugin for any store or business. Common use cases include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ecommerce sellers</li>\n<li>Course creators</li>\n<li>Membership platforms</li>\n<li>Freelancers and consultants</li>\n<li>Marketing agencies</li>\n<li>Small business owners</li>\n<li>Service providers</li>\n<li>Event planners and event organizers</li>\n<li>Digital product vendors</li>\n<li>Health and wellness professionals</li>\n<li>Dropshippers</li>\n<li>Nonprofits and charities</li>\n<li>Local businesses</li>\n<li>Financial advisors</li>\n<li>Software companies</li>\n<li>Fashion and apparel brands</li>\n<li>Fitness coaches</li>\n<li>Authors and publishers</li>\n<li>Subscription box providers</li>\n<li>Personal brands and bloggers</li>\n<li>Real estate professionals</li>\n<li>Educational institutions</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>🔗 Works Great With</h3>\n<p>CartFlows is designed to work seamlessly alongside these powerful companion plugins:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woo-cart-abandonment-recovery/\" rel=\"ugc\"><strong>Cart Abandonment Recovery</strong></a> for WooCommerce – Recover lost sales automatically by sending timed email sequences to shoppers who left without completing checkout. Pair with CartFlows to capture abandonment across every step of your funnel.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/modern-cart/\" rel=\"ugc\"><strong>Modern Cart for WooCommerce</strong></a> – Add a beautiful slide-out cart, floating cart icon, in-cart upsells, and a free shipping progress bar to your WooCommerce store. The perfect companion to CartFlows for a complete pre-to-post checkout funnel experience.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/power-coupons/\" rel=\"ugc\"><strong>Power Coupons for WooCommerce</strong></a> – Automatically apply discount rules at checkout based on cart conditions—no coupon codes required. Works alongside CartFlows&#8217; checkout to create smooth, incentivized buying experiences.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/variation-swatches-woo/\" rel=\"ugc\"><strong>Variation Swatches for WooCommerce</strong></a> – Replace boring WooCommerce dropdown variation selectors with visual color swatches, image thumbnails, and text labels. Makes product selection faster and more intuitive—especially on CartFlows checkout pages with variable products.</p>\n<h3>Supported Themes, Plugins and Tools</h3>\n<p><strong>Themes</strong><br />\nCartFlows works with any WooCommerce-compatible theme, including:</p>\n<p>➡️ Astra<br />\n➡️ Spectra One<br />\n➡️ Avada<br />\n➡️ Blocksy<br />\n➡️ Divi<br />\n➡️ Flatsome<br />\n➡️ GeneratePress<br />\n➡️ Hello Elementor<br />\n➡️ Hestia<br />\n➡️ Kadence<br />\n➡️ Neve<br />\n➡️ OceanWP<br />\n➡️ Phlox<br />\n➡️ PopularFX<br />\n➡️ Storefront<br />\n➡️ Woostify<br />\n➡️ Zakra</p>\n<p><strong>Page Builders</strong><br />\nCartFlows works with any page builder compatible with WooCommerce, including:</p>\n<p>➡️ Spectra<br />\n➡️ Elementor<br />\n➡️ Divi Builder<br />\n➡️ Bricks Builder<br />\n➡️ Beaver Builder<br />\n➡️ Brizy Builder<br />\n➡️ Thrive Architect<br />\n➡️ Gutenberg<br />\n➡️ Oxygen Builder</p>\n<p><strong>Payment Gateways</strong><br />\nCartFlows works with any WooCommerce-compatible payment gateway, including:</p>\n<p>➡️ Stripe Payments for WooCommerce by Checkout Plugins<br />\n➡️ PayPal Payments for WooCommerce by Checkout Plugins<br />\n➡️ WooCommerce Stripe Payment Gateway<br />\n➡️ PayPal Express Checkout<br />\n➡️ WooCommerce Payments<br />\n➡️ PayPal Payments<br />\n➡️ Mollie<br />\n➡️ Square<br />\n➡️ Auth.Net<br />\n➡️ Direct Bank Transfer (BACS)</p>\n<p><strong>Other Compatible Plugins</strong></p>\n<p>➡️ Cart Abandonment Recovery for WooCommerce<br />\n➡️ Power Coupons for WooCommerce<br />\n➡️ Modern Cart for WooCommerce<br />\n➡️ Variation Swatches for WooCommerce<br />\n➡️ SureMembers<br />\n➡️ LearnDash<br />\n➡️ TutorLMS<br />\n➡️ LifterLMS<br />\n➡️ MemberPress<br />\n➡️ LearnPress<br />\n➡️ Wishlist Member<br />\n➡️ FluentForms<br />\n➡️ AliDropship<br />\n➡️ OttoKit</p>\n<p><strong>Integrations</strong><br />\nCartFlows integrates with 1,000+ apps and services via OttoKit—including Asana, AirTable, Gmail, Slack, Mailchimp, ActiveCampaign, and thousands more.</p>\n<h3>👥 Connect with Our Team and Community</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/cartflows/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\"><strong>Facebook Group</strong></a>: Join our active community for tips, tricks, and updates.</li>\n</ul>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:286:\"<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>cartflows.zip</code> to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the <strong>Plugins</strong> menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Make sure to <strong>disable caching</strong> on your checkout and thank you step pages</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:13267:\"\n<dt id=\"what%20is%20a%20sales%20funnel%20and%20a%20funnel%20builder%3F\">\nWhat is a sales funnel and a funnel builder?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>A sales funnel is a series of steps that guides a buyer from browsing to purchase—and beyond. A WordPress funnel builder like CartFlows makes it easy to create conversion-optimized funnels directly inside WordPress, without needing separate SaaS tools. With CartFlows, you can build complete sales funnels including landing pages, checkout pages, one-click upsell offers, and thank you pages—all from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"is%20cartflows%20a%20good%20clickfunnels%20alternative%20for%20wordpress%3F\">\nIs CartFlows a good ClickFunnels alternative for WordPress?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes—CartFlows is one of the most popular ClickFunnels alternatives for WordPress users. While ClickFunnels charges $97–$297/month, CartFlows runs on your own WordPress site with no monthly SaaS fees. You get all the core features: unlimited funnels, order bumps, one-click upsells, A/B testing, and analytics—plus full WooCommerce integration. It&#8217;s the choice of 200,000+ stores that want funnel-builder power without the SaaS price tag.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20makes%20cartflows%20different%20from%20other%20woocommerce%20funnel%20builders%3F\">\nWhat makes CartFlows different from other WooCommerce funnel builders?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows is your all-in-one WordPress funnel builder and WooCommerce checkout plugin. Here&#8217;s what sets it apart:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Replace the default WooCommerce checkout entirely with a modern, conversion-optimized page</li>\n<li>Build unlimited personalized sales funnels for specific products or categories</li>\n<li>Works with all major page builders—Elementor, Bricks, Divi, Beaver, Spectra, Gutenberg</li>\n<li>One-click import of professionally designed sales funnel templates</li>\n<li>Add upsells, downsells, and order bumps with smart rule-based conditions</li>\n<li>Built-in analytics, A/B testing, pixel tracking, and automation support</li>\n<li>Trusted by 200,000+ stores—the #1 most-installed WordPress funnel builder</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20is%20required%20to%20use%20cartflows%3F\">\nWhat is required to use CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows requires WordPress and WooCommerce to be installed on your site. No additional tools, platforms, or monthly SaaS subscriptions are needed. Once activated, CartFlows works directly within your existing WordPress setup.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"does%20cartflows%20support%20one-page%20checkout%20for%20woocommerce%3F\">\nDoes CartFlows support one-page checkout for WooCommerce?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes! CartFlows supports multiple WooCommerce checkout layouts including one-column (single page), two-column, two-step, multi-step, and the Instant Checkout layout—a fully distraction-free, conversion-optimized checkout designed to maximize completions. You can choose whichever layout best fits your store and audience.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"how%20do%20i%20replace%20the%20woocommerce%20checkout%20page%20with%20cartflows%3F\">\nHow do I replace the WooCommerce checkout page with CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows makes it easy to replace the default WooCommerce checkout. Simply activate CartFlows, select the &#8220;Store Checkout&#8221; option in the CartFlows settings, and choose or import a checkout template. CartFlows will automatically override the default WooCommerce checkout page and serve your custom, conversion-optimized checkout to every shopper. No coding required.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"does%20cartflows%20work%20with%20my%20page%20builder%3F\">\nDoes CartFlows work with my page builder?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Absolutely. CartFlows integrates seamlessly with all major page builders including Spectra, Elementor, Bricks Builder, Divi, Beaver Builder, Brizy, Thrive Architect, Gutenberg, and Oxygen Builder. Every page builder gets dedicated blocks, widgets, or modules for CartFlows checkout forms, upsell buttons, order detail blocks, and opt-in forms.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20type%20of%20funnels%20can%20i%20create%20with%20cartflows%3F\">\nWhat type of funnels can I create with CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows is highly flexible and supports virtually any type of WordPress sales funnel, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lead generation and opt-in funnels</li>\n<li>Squeeze page funnels</li>\n<li>WooCommerce checkout replacement funnels</li>\n<li>Product launch funnels</li>\n<li>Tripwire sales funnels</li>\n<li>Membership sales funnels</li>\n<li>Online course funnels (with LearnDash, TutorLMS, LifterLMS)</li>\n<li>Subscription-based funnels</li>\n<li>Free and paid webinar funnels</li>\n<li>Affiliate marketing funnels</li>\n<li>Hybrid multi-step funnels</li>\n<li>Cross-sell and upsell funnels</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"can%20i%20sell%20online%20courses%20using%20cartflows%3F\">\nCan I sell online courses using CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes! CartFlows integrates with leading LMS plugins including LearnDash, TutorLMS, LifterLMS, LearnPress, and MemberPress. You can build dedicated course sales funnels, add order bumps for course upgrades, and use one-click upsells to enroll students into additional courses immediately after checkout.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20is%20the%20instant%20checkout%20layout%3F\">\nWhat is the Instant Checkout Layout?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>The Instant Checkout Layout is CartFlows&#8217; most conversion-focused WooCommerce checkout experience. It creates a distraction-free, fully branded checkout page—with no site header, footer, or navigation links—keeping buyers focused entirely on completing their purchase. It&#8217;s auto-enabled when you create a new funnel, so you&#8217;re always starting with the highest-converting layout.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20are%20order%20bumps%2C%20and%20how%20do%20they%20work%20in%20cartflows%3F\">\nWhat are order bumps, and how do they work in CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Order bumps are small, targeted add-on offers placed directly on the WooCommerce checkout page—below the product summary and above the &#8220;Place Order&#8221; button. Customers can accept them with a single click, without leaving the checkout flow. CartFlows Pro supports dynamic order bumps with rule-based conditions (cart total, products, categories), multiple modern order bump styles, and custom placement options. Order bumps typically increase average order value by 10–30%.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20is%20smart%20funnel%20routing%3F\">\nWhat is Smart Funnel Routing?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Smart Funnel Routing (Pro) is CartFlows&#8217; intelligence layer for upsell paths. Instead of showing the same upsell to every customer, Smart Funnel Routing uses cart contents and purchase history to dynamically direct each buyer to the most relevant upsell offer. This means the right offer reaches the right customer at the right time—increasing conversion rates across your entire funnel.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"how%20does%20cartflows%20handle%20abandoned%20carts%3F\">\nHow does CartFlows handle abandoned carts?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows works hand-in-hand with <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woo-cart-abandonment-recovery/\" rel=\"ugc\">WooCommerce Cart Abandonment Recovery</a>—a free companion plugin that tracks shoppers who leave checkout without completing their purchase and automatically sends timed recovery email sequences. You can customize email content, delays, and discount incentives to bring buyers back and recover lost revenue.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"can%20i%20auto-apply%20discounts%20or%20coupons%20in%20cartflows%3F\">\nCan I auto-apply discounts or coupons in CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes. CartFlows Pro includes Auto Apply Coupons—discounts are applied automatically at checkout when conditions are met, no code entry required. For more advanced discount rules (category-based offers, quantity breaks, spend-to-unlock incentives), pair CartFlows with <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/power-coupons/\" rel=\"ugc\">Power Coupons for WooCommerce</a>—a rule-based discount engine that triggers offers automatically as the cart updates.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"can%20i%20add%20visual%20product%20variation%20swatches%20to%20cartflows%20checkout%20pages%3F\">\nCan I add visual product variation swatches to CartFlows checkout pages?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes! If you&#8217;re selling variable products (sizes, colors, materials), you can use <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/variation-swatches-woo/\" rel=\"ugc\">Variation Swatches for WooCommerce</a> alongside CartFlows. It replaces the default WooCommerce dropdown variation selectors with visual color swatches, image thumbnails, and text labels—making product selection faster and more intuitive on your CartFlows checkout pages.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"does%20cartflows%20support%20a%2Fb%20testing%3F\">\nDoes CartFlows support A/B testing?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes. CartFlows Pro includes A/B split testing for any page in your funnel—checkout pages, upsell offers, order bumps, headlines, and CTAs. Split traffic between variants, track conversion rates and revenue per variant, and confidently roll out the winner. Data-driven funnel optimization has never been easier.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"does%20cartflows%20provide%20analytics%20tools%3F\">\nDoes CartFlows provide analytics tools?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes. CartFlows includes a unified analytics and insights dashboard where you can track conversions, revenue, average order value, and step-by-step funnel performance. The Pro version adds deeper per-step revenue tracking, revenue per visit metrics, and date-range filtering—giving you everything you need to identify and fix underperforming funnel steps.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"how%20does%20cartflows%20support%20social%20media%20pixel%20tracking%3F\">\nHow does CartFlows support social media pixel tracking?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows has built-in native support for Facebook Pixel, Google Analytics (UA &amp; GA4), Pinterest Pixel, Snapchat Pixel, and TikTok Pixel. Track checkout events, upsell acceptances, and thank-you page views across all your ad platforms—no third-party plugin required. This gives you accurate retargeting data and cleaner ad attribution.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"what%20payment%20gateways%20does%20cartflows%20support%3F\">\nWhat payment gateways does CartFlows support?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows works with any WooCommerce-compatible payment gateway. This includes Stripe, PayPal, Square, Mollie, Auth.Net, WooCommerce Payments, iDEAL, and Direct Bank Transfer. For one-click upsells specifically, CartFlows supports Stripe, PayPal, Square, Mollie, WooCommerce Payments, and Cash on Delivery.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"does%20cartflows%20support%20subscription%20payments%3F\">\nDoes CartFlows support subscription payments?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes. CartFlows is fully compatible with the WooCommerce Subscriptions extension. CartFlows Pro also includes enhanced subscription handling features—including auto-payment retries and proration for plan upgrades—making it easy to manage recurring revenue funnels.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"can%20cartflows%20automate%20post-purchase%20tasks%3F\">\nCan CartFlows automate post-purchase tasks?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes. CartFlows integrates with OttoKit (formerly SureTriggers) to automate workflows triggered by funnel events—send thank you emails, tag customers in your CRM, notify your team on Slack, add contacts to Mailchimp lists, and more. OttoKit connects CartFlows to 1,000+ apps and services, making full marketing automation possible without leaving WordPress.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"how%20many%20funnels%20can%20i%20create%20with%20cartflows%3F\">\nHow many funnels can I create with CartFlows?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>With the free version of CartFlows, you can create multiple sales funnels to get started. For unlimited funnels, advanced features like one-click upsells, dynamic order bumps, A/B testing, smart funnel routing, and premium support, upgrade to CartFlows Pro—plans start at just $16/month, a fraction of what SaaS funnel builders charge.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"which%20themes%20does%20cartflows%20work%20with%3F\">\nWhich themes does CartFlows work with?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>CartFlows works with any WordPress theme. It has been tested and confirmed compatible with Astra, Avada, Blocksy, Divi, Flatsome, GeneratePress, Hello Elementor, Kadence, Neve, OceanWP, Storefront, and many more. If you run into any theme-specific issue, our support team is ready to help.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"i%27m%20new%20to%20cartflows.%20where%20can%20i%20find%20documentation%3F\">\nI&#8217;m new to CartFlows. Where can I find documentation?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Welcome! Visit our <a href=\"https://cartflows.com/docs/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">comprehensive documentation</a> to learn how to build high-converting WooCommerce funnels step by step. You can also connect with us here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cartflows.com/support/open-a-ticket/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Open a Support Ticket</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/cartflows\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Join the CartFlows Community</a></li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<dt id=\"how%20can%20i%20report%20a%20security%20vulnerability%3F\">\nHow can I report a security vulnerability?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>We take plugin security extremely seriously. If you discover a vulnerability, please report it responsibly through our <a href=\"https://brainstormforce.com/bug-bounty-program/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Bug Bounty Program</a>. Do not disclose security issues publicly.</p>\n</p>\n\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:22474:\"<h4>Version 3.1.2 &#8211; Friday, 26th June 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Redesigned the weekly performance report email with a cleaner layout and new sections for weekly tips, top wins, and quick action links.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced Instant Checkout integration so the layout wrapper renders correctly before third-party payment buttons such as Stripe Express Checkout.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Steps Analytics now displays A/B test variations and archived step rows so historical performance stays visible at a glance.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Refined Analytics chart Y-axis with compact number and currency formatting.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the Funnel filter dropdown truncating long funnel names on the Analytics screen.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed dropdown field overlap on product rows inside the Checkout product settings.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the trend line rendering outside the chart area on Analytics graphs.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed Select2 dropdown height mismatch on the Checkout page with WooCommerce 9.7.1 and above.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a PHP notice for the Pre-Checkout Offer setting on CartFlows Free with PHP 8 and above.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 3.1.1 &#8211; Tuesday, 2nd June 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Smoother step card interactions on the funnel canvas — uniform sizing and clearer hover feedback.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a PHP deprecation notice triggered when saving checkout step products on PHP 8.1 and above.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 3.1.0 &#8211; Monday, 1st June 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Introduced a redesigned Funnel Canvas for a cleaner and more intuitive funnel-building experience.</li>\n<li>New: Added a Funnel Performance widget to the WordPress Dashboard with a quick 30-day summary of orders and revenue.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced a new filter to optionally restrict adding the same product more than once on a checkout step.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Improved the Funnels page load performance by preventing duplicate data fetch requests.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Refined the usage data consent label on the setup wizard and onboarding to clearly highlight its benefits.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the View Funnel button opening the site home page instead of the first step of the funnel.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the Checkout step editor crashing when a selected product variation was deleted from WooCommerce.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed Beaver Builder step templates importing as blank pages.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the Razorpay &#8216;Something went wrong&#8217; popup appearing on the Instant Layout thank you page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the thank you page access restriction blocking funnel preview when test mode was enabled.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved PHP deprecation notices shown on the setup wizard with WordPress 6.4 and above.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 3.0.1 &#8211; Friday, 1st May 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Refined admin UI for a more polished experience.</li>\n<li>Security Fix: Hardened the security of the plugin.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed Checkout Offer settings showing a blank page when selecting a product.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed Store Checkout floating labels not visible after filling fields.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed BSF Analytics loader and Learn tab completed modules tracking.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed THWCFE custom checkbox and radio fields not displaying correctly on Store Checkout.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 3.0.0 &#8211; Monday, 27th April 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Revamped admin experience across Dashboard, Funnels, Steps, Analytics, Settings, and more for faster navigation.</li>\n<li>New: Redesigned onboarding wizard for a quicker, more intuitive setup.</li>\n<li>New: Added toast notifications for instant action feedback.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced Error Boundary UI for better error handling and quick recovery.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Improved filters, bulk actions, pagination, and breadcrumbs for smoother funnel management.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved various UI, UX, and functionality issues for a smoother experience.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.2.4 &#8211; Wednesday, 25th March 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Added Power Coupons to the Addons page for quick access and activation.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced WordPress Abilities API integration to enable AI-powered automation for CartFlows.</li>\n<li>Security Fix: Hardened the security of the plugin.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed Store Checkout setting not persisting on WordPress Multisite subsites.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.2.3 &#8211; Tuesday, 10th March 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Added a new layout for the Thank You page.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced CartFlows native webhook integration.</li>\n<li>New: Added global custom JavaScript and CSS support, allowing users to add custom scripts across all funnels.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Introduced separate Code Editors for JavaScript and CSS, replacing the textarea used for custom scripts in Funnels and Steps settings.</li>\n<li>Fix: Checkout: Fixed WooCommerce Stripe Express Checkout button misalignment in the Modern Checkout layout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Checkout: Fixed order summary position setting not being applied on the frontend when Instant Layout is enabled for checkout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed JSON response error in the block editor while updating a CartFlows step.</li>\n<li>Fix: Checkout: Fixed missing checkmark for Order Bump when positioned before the checkout form with Instant Layout enabled.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed dashboard icon and layout misalignment in the admin menu.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.2.2 &#8211; Tuesday, 24th February 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Added Learn tab with guided setup to help users understand and configure core CartFlows features.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced Order Pay page template for Store Checkout.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Added toggle setting to enable or disable steps in the backend.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Checkout: Added file input field support in the Custom Editor within Checkout step settings.</li>\n<li>Fix: Checkout: Fixed preview not opening in full screen in Checkout Offer settings in the backend.</li>\n<li>Fix: Checkout: Improved UX for the Dynamic Offers product condition setting in the backend.</li>\n<li>Fix: Checkout: Fixed an issue for missing favicon on Instant Checkout in the frontend.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.2.1 &#8211; Wednesday, 4th February 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Introduced Tutor LMS compatibility allowing non-enrolled users to be redirected to CartFlows templates.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Introduced the <code>cartflows_allow_remove_permalink_base</code> filter to allow removal of the permalink base from CartFlows funnel URLs.</li>\n<li>Fix: Prevented duplicate products from being added in checkout product settings in the backend.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.2.0 &#8211; Tuesday, 27th January 2026</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Security Fix: Hardened the security of the plugin suggested by PatchStack.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Added new unified analytics screens for easier funnel performance tracking.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the Order Bump description did not update in real time.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a conflict where Smart Coupons actions failed to add products via coupons.</li>\n<li>Fix: Removed PHP deprecation notices when using Bricks Builder on multisite.</li>\n<li>Fix: Prevented step titles from redirecting to the page builder editor when using Instant Layout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Corrected date filter issues on the funnel admin page.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.19 &#8211; Monday, 22nd December 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the order review section not visible by default in instant layout.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.18 &#8211; Monday, 22nd December 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Eliminated redundant backend API calls when fetching funnel data during funnel editing.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed Dutch billing address formatting issues caused by Google Address Autocomplete after page refresh.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved the dashboard stats AJAX warning that occurred during stats retrieval.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed <code>_load_textdomain_just_in_time</code> notices triggered by internal libraries.</li>\n<li>Fix: Prevented the selected shipping method from being cleared when changing the address on the checkout page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a conflict with CartFlows and LearnDash where course descriptions failed to display after saving.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed an issue where the Thank You page displayed both main and upsell products despite Replace Main Order was enabled.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed custom logo behavior on instant layout styles so it renders as expected.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed an issue where the CartFlows Thank You page failed to display when using the WebToffee PayPal Gateway.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the DatePicker selected the previous day when choosing past dates.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.17 &#8211; Monday, 17th November 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Updated Google Fonts for improved consistency.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Improved the Funnel Status toggle to make it more intuitive.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced Funnel Test Mode by adding a dropdown for better usability.</li>\n<li>Fix: Removed non-CartFlows revenue from the dashboard graph to ensure accurate reporting.</li>\n<li>Fix: Removed cancelled-order revenue from the dashboard graph for correct revenue totals.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the Confirmation dialog failing to save Order Bump settings after confirmation.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed custom CSS added within custom scripts settings not being applied issue.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.16 &#8211; Tuesday, 14th October 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Resolved the duplicate image issue while importing a ready-made template.</li>\n<li>Fix: Improved code performance by fixing the Rollback feature transient cache mismatch.</li>\n<li>Fix: Improved UI/UX and mobile responsiveness on the CartFlows Dashboard and Conditional Order Bump panel.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.15 &#8211; Tuesday, 22nd July 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Addressed a conflict with LearnDash and the Classic Editor plugin.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved issues in the onboarding flow for a smoother setup experience.</li>\n<li>Fix: Page Builder and Permalink options were not saving correctly on WordPress Multisite installations.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.14 &#8211; Thursday, 26th June 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Funnel import from a JSON file is now possible even when no funnels exist, as the Import button is displayed.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the issue of image render on Instant Checkout Thank you page.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.13 &#8211; Monday, 16th June 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced the Create New Product popup for a better user experience.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the Order Bump stayed selected after the product was removed when cart editing on checkout was enabled.</li>\n<li>Fix: Exported funnel JSON files now include previously missing funnel settings data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.12 &#8211; Wednesday, 21st May 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Improved the toggle button with improved handling of disabled states, making the toggle button more intuitive and user-friendly.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Added compatibility for future release of CartFlows Pro.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.11 &#8211; Tuesday, 13th May 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Added option to upload a custom logo in the header of the Instant Layout style.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced tooltips across the interface for better clarity.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a critical error caused by the latest update of the WooCommerce Stripe Gateway.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed an issue where the &#8220;What&#8217;s New&#8221; notification was not being displayed.</li>\n<li>Fix: Purchase event was not being tracked correctly for Facebook — now fixed.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved dropdown overlap issue with country and state field labels.</li>\n<li>Fix: Slide-out panel now closes properly when clicking outside the panel area.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed styling issues for navigation tabs in the Order Bump and Checkout Offer settings panels.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a conflict with shipping methods when using the DPD Blastic shipping plugin on CartFlows Checkout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed checkout field order conflict with the PostNL plugin in CartFlows.</li>\n<li>Fix: Shipping options now display correctly without needing to refresh the checkout page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Custom content was not appearing on the Instant Layout of the Thank You page — now resolved.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.10 &#8211; Wednesday, 9th April 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: SureTriggers is now OttoKit. We&#8217;ve updated the compatibility to keep everything working smoothly.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Instant Layout will be auto-enabled when users create a funnel from scratch. This will help users get a ready-made structure right away.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Improved design of Store Checkout pop-up</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.9 &#8211; Thursday, 3rd April 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Introduced a new style for thank you page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Corrected the price display on the Instant Layout of the Thank You page when tax is enabled.</li>\n<li>Fix: Improved UX and mobile responsiveness on the step&#8217;s template library page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed an error when adding an order bump product in step settings.</li>\n<li>Fix: Ensured billing and shipping details are displayed for all users on the Thank You page, not just logged-in users.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the incorrect order number was shown on the Instant Layout of the Thank You page when using the Sequential Order Numbers plugin.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.8 &#8211; Wednesday, 5th March 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Introduced language files for multiple languages for quick translation of the plugin.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved issue preventing step pages from being edited with Oxygen Builder.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved the conflict between CartFlows and custom templates of Bricks Builder on Shop page.</li>\n<li>Fix: The funnel&#8217;s GCP colors were not getting imported while importing the ready-made templates.</li>\n<li>Fix: Removed the extra spacing at the bottom of the page while using the instant checkout layout on mobile devices.</li>\n<li>Fix: The product image is not displaying properly for iOS mobile devices for instant checkout layout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Corrected the issue where the next step button was active in the page builder&#8217;s editor view, causing redirect problems during page editing.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved UI/UX problems on the create new from scratch screen.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Introduced a setup status checklist feature on the CartFlows dashboard.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Displaying the selected product&#8217;s information on the opt-in page consistently with the checkout page.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced the custom field creation process with inline error messages.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced the mobile experience of CartFlows Dashboard and Flow Listing page.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Improved the onboarding steps to let the user complete the required steps to help setup the CartFlows easily.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.7 &#8211; Friday, 24th January 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a critical issue caused by a missing compatibility class for the fix implemented for Oxygen Builder on the Thank You page.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.6 &#8211; Thursday, 23rd January 2025</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Introduced the Rollback feature for CartFlows.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced block previews in Gutenberg for better clarity.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Removed the General Panel from Landing step settings for a cleaner interface.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Displayed product details in the Product Dropdown for easier selection.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Modified the &#8220;No Access&#8221; message on the global settings popup for better communication.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Updated the NPS Library for improved functionality.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Added CartFlows branding to page builder widgets/blocks.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved inconsistent style issues in the Store Checkout and Subscribe Tabs on onboarding pages.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed color customization inconsistencies for checkout form fields.</li>\n<li>Fix: Addressed a conflict with the Convert Pro plugin on the onboarding screen.</li>\n<li>Fix: Changed the date picker theme to Light Mode for consistency.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed display issues on the onboarding screen for the Automations page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Turned off the &#8220;Required&#8221; toggle when the &#8220;Enable&#8221; toggle is disabled in the Field Editor.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved CSS issues affecting the empty cart message block on the checkout page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Allowed decimal values in the discount field for Checkout, Upsell, and Downsell steps.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where SVG files failed to upload in Elementor templates, leading to blank image displays.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed responsive issues for Instant Checkout on slightly larger tablets.</li>\n<li>Fix: Addressed a CSS issue for Payment Options on Checkout Page with WooPayments.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a conflict with the Speedy &#8211; WooCommerce Shipping Method plugin.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.5 &#8211; Wednesday, 25th December 2024</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where Instant Checkout design styles were not applying to the coupon button.</li>\n<li>Fix: Added onboarding steps to simplify selecting and importing the Instant Checkout layout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Updated the color picker component to enhance usability and address UX issues.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the step settings slide-out panel unexpectedly closing when changing the step title or adding a custom field.</li>\n<li>Fix: Unable to select &#8216;Less than or equal to&#8217; dropdown option in the dynamic offers.</li>\n<li>Fix: The product options does not get saved when it is collapsed or close the settings panel.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.4 &#8211; Tuesday, 10th December 2024</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: What&#8217;s New Feed: Added a feature to view the latest updates for the CartFlows plugin directly in the dashboard.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Updated the &#8220;Activate License&#8221; section to clearly display the license status.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Excluded &#8220;Out of Stock&#8221; products from the product list when selecting items for Checkout or Upsell steps.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the saved checkmark remained after reopening the Settings popup.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a problem where selecting inactive page builders redirected users to a blank screen.</li>\n<li>Fix: Adjusted the &#8220;Choose Step&#8221; dropdown width to prevent text overflow on smaller screens.</li>\n<li>Fix: Updated the origin column to show &#8220;Direct&#8221; for Upsell/Downsell orders instead of &#8220;Unknown.&#8221;</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a UI issue where the border of the discount input field appeared broken.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the Save button remained stuck in a loading state when the quantity field was set to 0.</li>\n<li>Fix: Prevented negative values from being accepted in the percentage discount field.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a bug where changes were not saved after confirming &#8220;Yes&#8221; in the save changes popup.</li>\n<li>Fix: Improved the visibility of the active checkout template and added a clear &#8220;Back&#8221; button for better navigation.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved a problem where toggle fields did not update immediately without refreshing the page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed the Scroll to Top icon issue for the Astra theme.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an incorrect usage error for the _load_textdomain_just_in_time function.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where shipping options appeared multiple times in the multistep checkout layout.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a bug preventing the CartFlows funnel landing page from being edited in Bricks Builder when set as the homepage.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the NPS survey appeared on fresh installs without any funnels created.</li>\n<li>Fix: Fixed a spacing issue in the Global Settings popup that caused the Social Tracking accordion to display incorrectly.</li>\n<li>Deprecated: The Step Note field is now marked as soft-deprecated across all steps.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.3 &#8211; Tuesday, 19th November 2024</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improvement: Improved the UI of CartFlows in-plugin notices for better user experience.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue where the order summary price failed to update on mobile after adding an Order Bump.</li>\n<li>Fix: Addressed a bug in the date filter that caused inaccuracies in analytics data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.2 &#8211; Wednesday, 13th November 2024</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Improved the display of express checkout block of Checkout Plugins &#8211; Stripe for WooCommerce for Instant Checkout layout.</li>\n<li>Fix: The next-step button UI of Two Step Checkout layout was not getting displayed properly after latest release of Elementor.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.1 &#8211; Wednesday, 13th November 2024</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Added new options in Funnel&#8217;s setting to allow configurable logo width and height settings, conditionally applied for block (FSE) themes.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved an issue with logo display on Instant Checkout pages when using the Bricks theme.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved issue with shipping methods not refreshing correctly on the checkout page.</li>\n<li>Fix: Improved CSS for shipping error messages for better readability and consistent styling in RTL and standard templates.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.0 &#8211; Thursday, 7th November 2024</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Instant Checkout &amp; Thank You Layouts for distraction free and conversion focused checkout experience.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced Bricks Builder integration to easily design and build CartFlows steps.</li>\n<li>New: Added support for Dynamic Content Tags in CartFlows steps using Bricks Builder.</li>\n<li>New: SureTriggers Integration for adding workflows for each steps if required.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced native support for Pinterest Pixel to track activities on CartFlows Optin, Landing, Checkout, and Thank You pages.</li>\n<li>New: Introduced native support for Snapchat Pixel to track activities on CartFlows Optin, Landing, Checkout, and Thank You pages.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced user experience by moving the Shipping Methods section below the checkout fields.</li>\n<li>Improvement: Enhanced slide-in content display consistency across different funnel steps and tabs.</li>\n<li>Fix: Resolved the issue of knowledge base articles not being found when searching with lowercase terms.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The full changelog is available <a href=\"https://cartflows.com/product/cartflows/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">here</a>.</p>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:965:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-1.gif?rev=3213006\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-1.gif?rev=3213006\" alt=\"Create a ready-made sales funnel.\"></a><p>Create a ready-made sales funnel.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-2.gif?rev=3213006\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-2.gif?rev=3213006\" alt=\"Add a product to your sales funnel.\"></a><p>Add a product to your sales funnel.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-3.gif?rev=3213006\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-3.gif?rev=3213006\" alt=\"View Dashboard for quick updates.\"></a><p>View Dashboard for quick updates.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-4.gif?rev=3213006\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-4.gif?rev=3213006\" alt=\"Quickly re-arrange the steps.\"></a><p>Quickly re-arrange the steps.</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:16188:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">不评价后台一直弹窗！</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/leoshum/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a8c53f34325d6e22bb6c254b3da9ecf08ce94b5f46368f302807d4aa5e376b01?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a8c53f34325d6e22bb6c254b3da9ecf08ce94b5f46368f302807d4aa5e376b01?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/leoshum/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">leoshum</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">June 23, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>不评价后台一直弹窗！这个设定很烦人，能不能优化下，比如24小时不再弹出</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Very good and useful</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/infosimples/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d89164e85e3e134ca4c2ec93f3781a0ccd1d19329866da9cd04a4e34d9937f1b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d89164e85e3e134ca4c2ec93f3781a0ccd1d19329866da9cd04a4e34d9937f1b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/infosimples/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Maurício Bylaardt Volker <small>(infosimples)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">June 11, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Very good and useful</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Nice for Checkout Page Customization</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/brainchildbd/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e8937752c5a2503cf22c921a5cdce5fe1bd183c25d02f7744f63e982dfbdf63c?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e8937752c5a2503cf22c921a5cdce5fe1bd183c25d02f7744f63e982dfbdf63c?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/brainchildbd/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">brainchildbd</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">May 18, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keep Working for the Best</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great Tool for Recovering Sales!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/makartman/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a6307563391a4c2445a355a452602a706b167aff43a23d79910d8fcd457363ea?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a6307563391a4c2445a355a452602a706b167aff43a23d79910d8fcd457363ea?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/makartman/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">makartman</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 30, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I love the <strong>Cart Abandonment Recovery for WooCommerce</strong> plugin! It effectively helps me recover lost sales by sending automated follow-up emails to customers. Since using it, my conversion rates have noticeably increased. Highly recommend for any WooCommerce store!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Good Plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/quanglinhnguyen/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8ae7ab68d883035aec5ecf6a7ad98c1c6da31a2611a527b4f7bd216cd0ea8f64?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8ae7ab68d883035aec5ecf6a7ad98c1c6da31a2611a527b4f7bd216cd0ea8f64?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/quanglinhnguyen/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">quanglinhnguyen</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 28, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The plugin works quite well, but the free version omits quite a few features, especially the option to customize the checkout page interface, which used to be available but is now quite difficult to find.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Worst decision of your life</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jxenarios/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/95d7eb3d81123546c60c60b604cf687bd6c11c11e8f02915d7e19d7308190193?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/95d7eb3d81123546c60c60b604cf687bd6c11c11e8f02915d7e19d7308190193?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jxenarios/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jxenarios</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 18, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>cant use unless adding another plugin to edit anything, so you need 2 plugins to use this</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>next, you cant do anything on free, so they push you upgrade to pro. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>once pro, no support on future releases, have to re-buy the plugin</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great Product, Great Service</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/toristory/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0e88c7f177e1436ee6dcf11d30ebed18167e910c4afaea354b0c280e05d9d3fc?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0e88c7f177e1436ee6dcf11d30ebed18167e910c4afaea354b0c280e05d9d3fc?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/toristory/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">toristory</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 11, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I originally picked CartFlows to make my checkout pages prettier, but I quickly fell in love with the funnel-building aspect of it. There was a minor snag when some of my checkout pages returned JSON errors and wouldn\'t save metadata, but thanks to the diligence and professionalism of the CartFlows team, the error was fixed and my funnel is now functional! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Everyone I spoke to on the team was helpful and patient. I highly recommend this product not only for the pretty funnels but also for the fabulous customer service. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great Resource</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/zhuoge/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f189f3f4a4e624f1e71ed180443409cc7aca0c460b4b27f5f2c29ee57f976ee4?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f189f3f4a4e624f1e71ed180443409cc7aca0c460b4b27f5f2c29ee57f976ee4?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/zhuoge/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">zhuoge</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 14, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Great Resource</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Support 10/10</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/osheta/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/286009ef8a91bed8bb7b491dea0cf4dcb1b18378a75cd1ce1816816a02c6869a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/286009ef8a91bed8bb7b491dea0cf4dcb1b18378a75cd1ce1816816a02c6869a?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/osheta/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">osheta</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 5, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I had a bug in my platform. In less than 24, I had a response and a emporal solution to keep going on my business.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Maria</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">CartFlows does exactly what it promises</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nuurhasan/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c82d2fd396f179fd421f87d7184774e4b29b182c4cc9a3b2bfc060b09563061?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c82d2fd396f179fd421f87d7184774e4b29b182c4cc9a3b2bfc060b09563061?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nuurhasan/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">nuurhasan</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 10, 2026</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I used CartFlows on my site to create a custom checkout workflow, and it solved a very specific headache I had. I wanted to bypass the default Add to Cart page entirely and send users straight into a streamlined checkout flow, and CartFlows handled this effortlessly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Setup was straightforward. If you need clean easy  flows CartFlows is a great choice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:145:\"1 WordPress funnel builder &amp; WooCommerce checkout plugin. Boost AOV with one-click upsells, order bumps &amp; high-converting checkout pages.\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:58:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/cartflows.3.1.2.zip\";s:14:\"upgrade_notice\";a:0:{}s:11:\"screenshots\";a:4:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:62:\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-1.gif?rev=3213006\";s:7:\"caption\";s:33:\"Create a ready-made sales funnel.\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:62:\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-2.gif?rev=3213006\";s:7:\"caption\";s:35:\"Add a product to your sales funnel.\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:62:\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-3.gif?rev=3213006\";s:7:\"caption\";s:33:\"View Dashboard for quick updates.\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:62:\"https://ps.w.org/cartflows/assets/screenshot-4.gif?rev=3